      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " seems to mean “violate this command,” since the alteration of a decree was a thing unheard of.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Hanged is literally crucified. Among the Persians crucifixion was generally the nailing of a body to a cross after decapitation; among the Assyrians it was transfixion or impalement. Here the “being set up” refers of course to the man, and not to the beam.",
